This paper deals with the impact of correlation between interferers on the performance of cellular systems, specifically on coverage probability and rate. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) as it involves analyzing the transmission of information over a wireless channel. The paper also deals with interference (cs.NI) and graph theory (cs.GT) as it involves analyzing the relationships between nodes in a cellular network. Additionally, the paper involves statistical inference (cs.SI) as it deals with analyzing the statistical properties of Nakagami-m distributed random variables. Finally, the paper involves mathematical modeling (cs.MM) as it uses mathematical expressions to compare the coverage probability and rate in different scenarios.
